#===--- Intro

This document details how to use these templates to generate project documentation for client viewing from a local filesystem.

#===--- Requirements

To run:-
CxxDoc from Ravl/SourceTools
  available from http://ravl.sourceforge.net, but only CxxDoc binary required
  
To view:-
  A web browser
  
#===--- Customizing

When starting a new project documentation system, make CxxDoc and Doc directories in the root directory of the project. Copy all the files from this directory (except this README) into the CxxDoc directory.
Edit the word PROJECT in the new files to match the name of the project to document (find using 'grep -r PROJECT *').

#===--- Building

Running builddocs.sh should now generate the documentation in the Doc directory.

